Then i'll be the odd man out here and only say happy happys to our fellow members in here this Canada day ,,,,  WHY ,,,,, because i think all the  people of this country right now should'nt keep letting our Canadian gorverment see us having  good old times as they will continue to beleive they are serving us well when they are not . Happy Hoping Day is all i'll say for now . Sure hope i don't get slamed to the boards for this one .

Lew you are so right my friend.  Alway a very special day for our family, it was on this day in 1960 that we saw Union Station. We are proud to be Canadian. And have contributed to her growth from day one. Today even better, we celebrate our granddaughter 1st birthday and Wed I fly out to see family in the old country for three weeks. I haven't been back in 40 years.  Have safe weekend. I'm bringing my pad and hopefully I can check in while having glass of wine!
